de: Addendum No 1 to the Project Agreement between Switzerland represented by the Swiss State Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) and the Republic of Poland represented by the Ministry of Regional Development as the National Coordination Unit (NCU) concerning the Grant for the Project KIK/48 "Infrastructure Upgrades in Public Buildings in the Parseta River Basin for an Improvement of Natural Environment Conditions"  - 29-10-2013 - Abkommen zwischen der Schweiz, vertreten durch das SECO, und Polen, vertreten durch das Ministerium für Regionalentwicklung, bezüglich der Förderung erneuerbarer Energiequellen in der Region des Parseta Flussbeckens, KIK/48
en: Addendum No 1 to the Project Agreement between Switzerland represented by the Swiss State Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) and the Republic of Poland represented by the Ministry of Regional Development as the National Coordination Unit (NCU) concerning the Grant for the Project KIK/48 "Infrastructure Upgrades in Public Buildings in the Parseta River Basin for an Improvement of Natural Environment Conditions"  - 29-10-2013 - Project Agreement between Switzerland represented by the Swiss State Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) and the Republic of Poland represented by the Ministry of Regional Development as the National Coordination Unit (NCU) concerning the Grant for the Project KIK/48 "Infrastructure Upgrades in Public Buildings in the Parseta River Basin for an Improvement of Natural Environment Conditions" - to be implemented during the period 1.11.2011 until 30.04.2014
fr: Addendum No 1 to the Project Agreement between Switzerland represented by the Swiss State Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) and the Republic of Poland represented by the Ministry of Regional Development as the National Coordination Unit (NCU) concerning the Grant for the Project KIK/48 "Infrastructure Upgrades in Public Buildings in the Parseta River Basin for an Improvement of Natural Environment Conditions"  - 29-10-2013 - Accord entre la Suisse, représentée par le SECO, et la Pologne, représentée par le Ministère du développement régional, concernant la promotion des sources d'énergies renouvelables à la région du bassin fluvial de Parseta, KIK/48
